  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Case-control studies and meta-analysis have reported that several fundus features, especially
      the thickness of the peripapillary retinal nerve fiber layer, are related to the brain
      degeneration and cognitive impairment. In our study, we aim to quantitatively assess retina
      features using OCT and define its associations with brain development and intelligence in
      children.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
